CREATED:20251204T142547Z
DESCRIPTION:We are delighted to invite you to the 2026 Duke Orthopaedics D
 epartmental Research Day & Symposium: Aligning Science and Society. This 
 annual event showcases the wide range\, depth\, and impact of research wi
 thin the Duke Orthopaedics Department-from basic science to clinical adva
 nces and community-engaged projects. \n\nThis year's program has been exp
 anded to highlight the full scope of scholarly activities in our departme
 nt. We look forward to your participation in celebrating the work of our 
 investigators\, trainees\, and staff as they advance orthopaedic science 
 and enhance musculoskeletal health.\n\nThe event includes:\n- Short Talks
  from undergraduate\, professional\, and graduate students\; clinical and
  research fellows\; APPs\; clinic staff\; administrators\; and faculty-al
 l illustrating the diversity of inquiry in orthopaedics.\n- Resident Pres
 entations featuring outstanding research led by residents.\n- Poster Sess
 ions displaying innovative work across basic\, translational\, clinical\,
  and population health research related to musculoskeletal care.\n\nJoin 
 us for a day of discovery\, collaboration\, and celebration as we showcas
 e the incredible breadth of research across our department.
DURATION:PT8H
