CREATED:20251204T204151Z
DESCRIPTION:Elizabeth Jones\, PhD\n\nDirector\, Education and Outreach\n\n
 Duke Office for Institutional Equity\n\n"Disability and Inclusive Excelle
 nce: Definitions\, context\, and best practices" \n\nThis interactive ses
 sion will discuss how disability shows up in the workplace and how we can
  ensure that everyone in our community is supported in their work. Partic
 ipants will be invited to explore disability as a form of human differenc
 e that touches all of our lives. We will discuss disability history\, phy
 sical disability\, neurodiversity\, increasing access\, and more. Partici
 pants will engage activities to deepen their knowledge about disability\,
  and their capacity to cultivate an ability inclusive workforce.\n\nHost:
  Saskia Hemmers\, PhD
DURATION:PT1H30M
DTSTAMP:20260304T192307Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260310T090000
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T192307Z
