DESCRIPTION:Learn the basics of keeping your data organized and reusable t
 hrough a combination of lecture and hands-on exercises. After attending t
 his workshop\, participants should be able to write a basic data manageme
 nt plan\, such as the one required for NIH applications\; develop a logic
 al filenaming and folder organization system\; and create a README to hel
 p others quickly open\, interpret\, and reuse their data. This event is o
 pen to non-Duke participants. This workshop qualifies for 200-level facul
 ty and staff RCR and Graduate School RCR credit.
DURATION:PT2H
